  "text": "The 'upstream connection pool overflow' condition in Envoy is triggered when the connection pool reaches resource limits and cannot create or allocate new connections. Here is a detailed breakdown of how this error is defined and handled:\n\n## Overflow State Definition\n\nThe overflow state is defined as an enum in `envoy/common/conn_pool.h` (lines 96-105). The `PoolFailureReason::Overflow` enum value represents a situation where a resource overflowed and policy prevented a new connection from being created.\n\n## Primary Points Where Overflow is Triggered\n\n### 1. Connection Pool Limit Exceeded\n**File**: `source/common/conn_pool/conn_pool_base.cc` (lines 127-164)\n**Function**: `ConnPoolImplBase::tryCreateNewConnection()`\n- Line 137-139: Increments `upstream_cx_overflow` counter when `canCreateConnection()` returns false due to the circuit breaker limit being reached\n\n### 2. Connection Pool Map Overflow\n**File**: `source/common/upstream/conn_pool_map_impl.h` (lines 24-61)\n**Function**: `ConnPoolMap<KEY_TYPE, POOL_TYPE>::getPool()`\n- Line 35-40: When a new connection pool is needed but all available pools are active and the resource limit cannot be expanded, it increments `upstream_cx_pool_overflow` counter and returns a null optional\n\n### 3. Max Streams/Requests Overflow\n**File**: `source/common/conn_pool/conn_pool_base.cc` (lines 175-181)\n**Function**: `ConnPoolImplBase::attachStreamToClient()`\n- Line 175-178: Checks if the maximum pending requests limit is reached and calls `onPoolFailure()` with `PoolFailureReason::Overflow`\n- Line 179: Increments `upstream_rq_pending_overflow_` counter\n- Line 176: Logs debug message \"max streams overflow\"\n\n## Overflow Handling Chain\n\n### HTTP Connection Pool Base\n**File**: `source/common/http/conn_pool_base.h` (lines 79-84)\n**Function**: `onPoolFailure()`\n- Receives the overflow failure reason and passes it to registered callbacks\n\n### TCP Connection Pool  \n**File**: `source/common/tcp/conn_pool.cc` (lines 196-202)\n**Function**: `ConnPoolImpl::onPoolFailure()`\n- Converts the ConnectionPool::PoolFailureReason to callbacks\n\n### Router Upstream Request Handling\n**File**: `source/common/router/upstream_request.cc` (lines 563-586)\n**Function**: `UpstreamRequest::onPoolFailure()`\n- Maps `ConnectionPool::PoolFailureReason::Overflow` to `Http::StreamResetReason::Overflow` (line 570)\n- Calls `onResetStream()` which triggers downstream response handling\n\n### Response Flag Setting\n**File**: `source/common/router/router.cc` (lines 1454-1479)\n**Function**: `Filter::streamResetReasonToResponseFlag()`\n- Line 1466-1467: Maps `StreamResetReason::Overflow` to `StreamInfo::CoreResponseFlag::UpstreamOverflow`\n- This flag is set in the stream info and can be seen in access logs\n\n## Additional Overflow Points\n\n### TCP Proxy\n**File**: `source/common/tcp_proxy/tcp_proxy.cc` (lines 471-474)\n- Line 472: Increments `upstream_cx_overflow_` when connection cannot be created\n\n### UDP Proxy Filter\n**File**: `source/extensions/filters/udp/udp_proxy/udp_proxy_filter.cc` (lines 144-147, 912-915)\n- Line 145 & 913: Increments `upstream_cx_overflow_` counter when session circuit breaker is exceeded\n\n## Counter Definitions\n\n**File**: `envoy/upstream/upstream.h` (lines 731-732)\n- `COUNTER(upstream_cx_overflow)` - Total times the cluster's connection circuit breaker overflowed\n- `COUNTER(upstream_cx_pool_overflow)` - Total times the cluster's connection pool circuit breaker overflowed\n\nThese counters are the observable metrics that appear in Envoy logs when traffic spikes cause the upstream connection pool to overflow."
}

